    "sections": [
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "Characterized by its charming timber houses, scattered holiday chalets, and hotels originating from the "
                },
                {
                    "type": "italic",
                    "value": "belle époque"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " era, this holiday retreat in the Bernese Oberland region preserves the quintessential essence of a picturesque mountain village. Facing southwest, its expansive terrace ensures an abundance of sunshine hours. Accessible since 1893 exclusively by the "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url": "https://www.jungfrau.ch/en-gb/corporate/jungfrau-railways/jungfraubahn-holding-ag/wengernalpbahn-ag/",
                    "value": "Wengernalp railway"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " (the world's longest cog railway) from "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "url": "/episodes/KJH0UZCgdhA/lauterbrunnen-switzerland-most-beautiful-place-in-switzerland",
                    "value": "Lauterbrunnen"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", Wengen has maintained its car-free status, with vehicles remaining parked in Lauterbrunnen."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "Wengen serves as a convenient hub for accessing prominent excursion spots within the Jungfrau region. Observation of climbers tackling the formidable Eiger north face, renowned as one of the world's most challenging climbing terrains, is possible through telescopes at "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url": "https://grindelwald.swiss/en/map/detail/kleine-scheidegg-9466bb35-976f-4a0d-a24a-5e22d9406816.html",
                    "value": "Kleine Scheidegg"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ". With a train transfer at Kleine Scheidegg, the "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "url": "/episodes/sQXi2iA0d_Q/jungfraujoch-the-top-of-europe-full-guide-unveiling-switzerlands-alpine-gem-4-k-uhd",
                    "value": "Jungfraujoch"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " can also be accessed via railway. Furthermore, from the valley floor resort of Lauterbrunnen, one can ascend to the summit of "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url": "https://schilthorn.swiss/",
                    "value": "Schilthorn"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " either through Mürren or Stechelberg."
                }
                
            ]
        },
