                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", visitors can journey to "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/THNVqfX3ZLnaPzhY6",
                    "value": "Interlaken-Ost"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ". Upon arrival, transitioning to the Bernese Oberland Railway facilitates the continuation of the journey to Lauterbrunnen. Subsequently, transferring to the Wengernalp Railway completes the final leg of the trip, allowing travelers to reach the charming village of Wengen."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "",
            "text": [
                
                {
                    "type": "bold",
                    "value": "By car (Wengen is car-free): "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "Travelers have multiple routes to reach "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "url": "/episodes/KLclTW2NH2g/interlaken-switzerland-beautiful-swiss-alps-main-attractions-to-visit-a-cinematic-short-film",
                    "value": "Interlaken"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", whether from Bern or Lucerne, or alternatively from the south via the Grimsel Pass (accessible in summer) or the Simplon Pass, followed by the Lötschberg car-transport train to Interlaken. Upon reaching Interlaken, signage directs travelers towards Grindelwald and Lauterbrunnen. Parking facilities are provided at the railway station. From there, taking the Wengernalp Railway enables access to the car-free village of Wengen."
                }
            ]
