        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "WHERE TO STAY",
            "titlelevel": 2,
            "text": [
                {
                    "type":"text",
                    "value": "If you plan to stay in Wengen for a couple of days, you will fin warm hospitality of the village's charming hotels, offering comfortable accommodations with unparalleled views of the surrounding peaks. We personally recommend the "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "class": "italic",
                    "url": "https://www.arenasresorts.com/en/wengen/",
                    "value": "Arenas Resort Victoria-Lauberhorn"
                },
                {
                    "type":"text",
                    "value": ", where we have already stayed once, in 2022, when we paid approximately "
                },
                {
                    "type":"bold",
                    "value": "CHF 150 for a Double Room with 2 single beds (90-130 cm wide), balcony, and mountain view (Jungfrau)."
                },
                {
                    "type":"text",
                    "value": " This resort offers unparalleled hospitality, very nice accommodations, and impeccable service, ensuring a truly memorable experience. Nestled amidst the captivating alpine scenery, with panoramic views of the majestic peaks, the resort provides the perfect retreat after a day of exploration and adventure."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "What to Do In Wengen",
            "titlelevel": 2,
            "text":[
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "As you explore this picturesque Swiss gem, specialy during winter, you'll discover a "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target":"_blank",
                    "url":"https://www.jungfrau.ch/en-gb/jungfrau-ski-region/",
                    "value": "plethora of activities"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " to indulge in, ensuring an unforgettable experience for every visitor. You can start your exploration with leisurely walks through the village's quaint streets, discover the "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "target":"_blank",
                    "url":"https://www.jungfrau.ch/en-gb/food-drink/",
                    "value": "local cuisine"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", or embark on amazing hiking trails featuring breathtaking mountain views."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type":"textimg",
            "img": {
                "url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/elbatista/wosdata/master/data/episodes/vM732ppJZog/assets/cousine.jpeg",
                "caption": "The amazing views of the trail from Männlichen to Wengen (photo by Alison Pang, Unsplash)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "Hiking Trails",
            "titlelevel": 3,
            "text": [
                {
                    "type":"text",
                    "value": "For an unforgettable alpine adventure that seamlessly combines scenic beauty with exploration, we highly recommend embarking on a hiking such as the ones bellow. Each route not only offers a leisurely hike, but also presents unparalleled vistas of the majestic Eiger, Mönch, and Jungfrau peaks."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "textimg",
            "title": "",
            "reverse":true,
            "img": {
                "url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/elbatista/wosdata/master/data/episodes/vM732ppJZog/assets/man-to-wengen.jpg",
                "style": {},
                "caption": "The amazing views of the trail from Männlichen to Wengen (photo by Alison Pang, Unsplash)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type":"richtext",
            "text":[
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "class": "font-bold uppercase tracking-wide",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url":"https://wengen.swiss/en/map/detail/mannlichen-03097adf-7871-48a1-a13b-ad7132922767.html",
                    "value": "Männlichen to Wengen:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " this trail offers a gradual descent, providing a gentle experience while granting a remarkable perspective of the surrounding peaks. Despite the captivating views, the broad pathway ensures safety, minimizing the risk of missteps. Upon reaching Kleine Scheidegg, though it's challenging to part ways with the breathtaking vista of the summit trio of Eiger, Mönch, and Jungfrau, the journey towards Wengen beckons. Following the railway track and the Lauberhornpiste, travelers descend effortlessly, relishing the enjoyable downward slope."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type":"richtext",
            "text":[
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class":"font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-xs md:text-sm",
                    "value": "Trail facts: "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class":"uppercase font-extralight text-xs md:text-sm",
                    "value": "Distance: 17.3 km | Duration: 3 h | Descent: 945 m | Difficulty: moderate"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type":"richtext",
            "text":[
                {
                    "type":"button",
                    "value":"video_camera_back",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url":"https://maennlichen.roundshot.com/",
                    "text":"See live webcam"
                }
            ]
        },
        
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "class": "font-bold uppercase tracking-wide",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url":"https://www.jungfrau.ch/en-gb/summer-sport/hiking/hiking-trail/lauberhorn-trail-23429704",
                    "value": "Lauberhorn Trail: "
                },
                {
                    "type":"text",
                    "value": "In the winter months, the Lauberhorn descent witnesses the thrilling spectacle of the fastest skiers hurtling down its slopes, completing the run in a mere two and a half minutes, reaching staggering speeds of 110 km/h on average. However, during the summer season, this iconic alpine ski racing route transforms into a serene landscape, inviting leisurely exploration on foot. It offers ample opportunity to soak in the breathtaking panorama of the Eiger, Mönch, and Jungfrau peaks, as well as to appreciate the sheer steepness of the slopes and the strategic highlights of the "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "class": "italic",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "url":"https://wengen.swiss/en/events/highlights/detail/international-lauberhorn-race.html",
                    "value": "World Cup course"
                },
                {
                    "type":"text",
                    "value": "."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "",
            "text": [
                {
                    "type":"text",
                    "value": "Traversing from the starting house, passing through the challenging Hundschopf and Brüggli-S sections, and descending to Wengen via the exhilarating Hanneggschuss, one can truly appreciate the intricacies of this daredevil slope. Information boards strategically placed along the route offer insights into the terrain and the challenges faced by the skiers. Only those who have embarked on this journey on foot can truly comprehend the courage required to tackle it on skis."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type":"richtext",
            "text":[
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class":"font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-xs md:text-sm",
                    "value": "Trail facts: "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class":"uppercase font-extralight text-xs md:text-sm",
                    "value": "Distance: 9.9 KM | Duration: 3.25 h | Descent: 1098 m | Difficulty: moderate."
                }
            ]
        },
